      "text": "The article \"Risiko auf alle Fälle\" (Risk by All Means)  is about political decisions in the face of the impossibility of even getting a grip on the unintended consequences of decisions for the future of society. [https://www.systemagazin.de/buecher/neuvorstellungen/2005/06/luhmann_short_cuts.php systemagazin.de] "
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "id": "327375ec3f1fae17",
      "text": "Decisions can therefore no longer be legitimized with authority based on nature, knowledge, or reason; \"controversy must take the form of dissolving certainty into uncertainty. There are no right choices, but only possibilities of difference-making entry into the circular determination of choice and future, possibilities of 'symmetry-breaking' and the establishment of irreversibility… And therefore it may be advisable to design choices in a trial style, to put them under revision, to orient them to learning possibilities, or to choose them in such a way that they generate more choices than they destroy\"."
    },
